A man who fled from authorities during a traffic stop was tracked down by a police helicopter due to his bright red underwear.

In a post and video on their Facebook page, the Seminole County Sheriff's Office told how they tracked the suspect as he ran away from the scene of a crash using the flash of colour as a guide.

Victor Tate, 30, of Lake Mary, has been charged with fleeing and eluding, reckless driving, possession of cocaine, possession of marijuana with intent to sell and driving without a valid license in the September 12 incident.

