Deputies said they attempted to stop Tate for speeding on State Road 434 in Longwood when he sped off. 

As they started a pursuit, Tate began accelerating to an estimated speed of 90 miles per hour and continued driving recklessly through traffic.

He lost control of the car and crashed into another vehicle at a traffic light on Lake Way Road and Greenwood Boulevard, according to the report.

